🏏 IPL Analysis using Pandas
This project is a data analysis of the Indian Premier League (IPL) using Pandas and Matplotlib. It includes data wrangling, exploratory data analysis (EDA), and various insights about IPL matches.

📌 Project Highlights
The IPL is played across 31 unique cities, giving a wide geographical spread to the tournament.

Data has been sorted and visualized using pandas.plot() for trend understanding.

Insights were drawn by grouping and analyzing team performances, match venues, and winning patterns.

🧠 Technologies Used
Python

Pandas

Matplotlib

Jupyter Notebook

